# Part I
## The Historical Record

{{imageMaskEdge6,--offset:10cm,--rotation:180
  ![Background image](https://github.com/PhantomDesk74/Homebrewery_Assets/blob/main/BookArt/History.png?raw=true){position:absolute,bottom:0,left:0,height:100%}
}}
\page
{{watermark WORK IN PROGRESS}}

{{pageNumber,auto}}

![Playlist Code](https://github.com/PhantomDesk74/Homebrewery_Assets/blob/main/BookArt/Grattum.png?raw=true) {position:absolute,bottom:50px,right:65px,width:250px,filter:opacity(70%);}
{{wide 
# The World of Grattum
}}

::

### Large Planet with Two Moons  
- Sil'Dorken
- Fal'Dormem (Formerly Fal'Doren)

### Peoples
- Denizens - **Grattari**
- Magical Universal Language - **Grattan**
  - Once learned, unlearn all other languages
  - Can understand all languages, can only speak Grattan

### Religion


Religion in Garttum is very much Science mixed with Spirits
- Grattari don't worship deities in the traditional sense.
- They worship the stars in they sky above them.
  - Rakkme (The Sun) The Raging Father
  - Sil'Dorken (Medium Moon, Desolate) The Dead Mother
  - Fal'Dormem/Fal'Doren (Small Moon, Sand)/(Small Moon, Lush) The Dormant Child/ The Living Child
:
Magic/Science Meld complete mix, T1 Civilization, moving to T2

Made Eternium Alloy - Obsidian/Adamantine Mix
Channels magic and engery better than any other substance.

## Infinitus Maxima
*Mega-Metropolis - 780M Residents*

Super masssive city that takes up nearly a quarter of the planets size. Eternum Pylons and Pilliars thorughout the city to coaless into a energy tractor beam. (No dyson sphere, but more siphon energy from sun into planet- Probably consistitutes T1.5 Civ)
:
4 Quadrants - Act as rings like from AoT
### Far Outer Ring - Mel'skett (The Frailty)
  - 32 Inner Disctricts (Slums, Communal living, Guardhouses, Agriculture, Access to Outlands)
#### **Sal'Gevas**
*(Created by Drew)*

A decedent oasis city in the middle of a desert. Drugs, prostitution and gambling are rife in this city of sin. The mayor of the city is a patsy for the true leaders of the city, an elven crime family.

#### **Semerang**
*(Created by Frank)*

Semerang is less a city and more an extensive collection of hovels built on top of each other on a pensinsula where sea water meets the mouth of a river. 

#### **Umovi**
*(Created by Alfredo)*

settlement depends on mages for food, magic centric community, magic sciency stuff motivated by greed to increase yield, town grows, makes a slum of people that cant afford efficient unethical magic. all because they settled a spot that cannot be reached by trade easy
### Middle Outer Ring - Ful'Murit (The Strength)
  - 16 Inner Disctricts
    - < need to figure out what goes here >
### Middle Inner Ring - Rakk'Mera (The Reach)
  - 8 Inner Disctricts
     - Main housing of the Eternium Pylons
     - Science houses, High Government, Worker housing
### Inner Ring - Sil'Herra (The Heart)
  - 4 Inner Disctricts
     - Nobility, Relgious Leadership, Military, Chosen of previous 3 houses
\page
### Class Changes
- Harnessers, Cyberbeasts, and Artificers created rifts to Fal'Doren when it was lush and created pylons on that moon as an anchor point.

#### Class Changes
- Barbarian - Wildkin
- Druid - Cyberbeast
- Fighter - Malechite
- Ranger/Rogue - Synth
- Artificer - unlocked
- Wizard - Harnesser
- Monk - Planetspeaker
- Paladin,Cleric,Bard,Warlock,Sorcerer - Unavailable
:
Wildkin, Cyberbeasts, and Planetspeakers formed a Sect of Society known as Land Dwellers. This class would be responsible for communing with nature and keeping the balance and order of Modern Civilization and Natural Essence of the world.
:
Malechites, Synths, and Harnessers formed the Nobles of Society, building vast structures and maintining the Mega Metropolis. Harnessers would weild the Weave itself as a blacksmith weilds a hammer. Synths would sow discourse in lower classes of civilization to keep them in order and under the heel of higher houses. Malechites would be the massive army of guards and muscle.

{{pageNumber,auto}}

The Grand Mistake
---------
When attempting to Harness the power of their sun, they channeled Weave Energies into the Eternium Plyons, attempting to suck the power of the sun to the planet. Using their Moon Fal'dormem as a conduit and gravity anchor, they would channel this concentrated beam towards their sun to finally achieve greatness. But in a grand act of espionage, the pylons on Fal'dormem were modified to be anchors instead of conduits, causing the power of the planet to instead pull the moon into itself. 

The ensuing panic and destruction caused the complete and total annihilation of Fal'dormem, Grattum, its people, and all life on the planet as was known. The only rememnant of the planet, was The Omega, the single Diety who watched as her only followers hubris was their ultimate downfall.


\page
