# Wildkin
:
big description of class and history

## Creating a Wildkin
To create a Wildkin, consult the following subsections, which give you hit points, proficiencies, and starting equipment. Then look at the Wildkin table to see which features you get at each level. The descriptions of those features appear in the “Wildkin Features” section.
\page
{{pageNumber,auto}}
<!--
## Class outline
- Barbarian - Wildkin
  - Subclass Name : Guider
    - Guider of the Winds
    - Guider of the Lands
    - Guider of the Stars
    - Guider of the Gods
-->
{{classTable,frame,decoration
##### The Wildkin
| Level | Proficiency Bonus | Features | Primal Essence | Primal Damage|
|:-----:|:-----------------:|:---------|:---------------------:|:-----:|
|  1st  |  +2  | Primal Essence, Unarmored Defense |          10            |1d4|
|  2nd  |  +2  | Essence Strike  |          10            |1d4|
|  3rd  |  +2  | Guide of the Wilds  |          10            |2d4|
|  4th  |  +2  | Ability Score Improvement |          10            |2d4|
|  5th  |  +3  | Extra Attack, Fast Movement  |          10            |2d6|
|  6th  |  +3  | Guider Feature      |          9            |2d6|
|  7th  |  +3  | Stalwart Guide  |          9            |3d8|
|  8th  |  +3  | Ability Score Improvement      |          9            |3d8|
|  9th  |  +4  | Destructive Might   |          8            |4d12|
| 10th  |  +4  | Guider Feature  |          8            |4d12|
| 11th  |  +4  |  Wild Fervor  |          7            |5d12|
| 12th  |  +4  | Ability Score Improvement   |          7             |5d12|
| 13th  |  +5  | Destructive Might  |          6             |3d20|
| 14th  |  +5  | Guider Feature  |          6             |3d20|
| 15th  |  +5  |  Eternal Essence |          5             |5d20|
| 16th  |  +5  | Ability Score Improvement   |          5             |5d20|
| 17th  |  +6  | Destructive Might |          4             |1d100|
| 18th  |  +6  | Guiders Offense |          3             |2d100|
| 19th  |  +6  | Ability Score Improvement        |          2             |3d100|
| 20th  |  +6  | Wildkin of Grattum   |          1             |1d500|
}}
### Quick Build
You can make a Wildkin quickly by following these suggestions. First, put your highest ability score in Strength, followed by Consitution or Wisdom. Second, choose the Outlander background
## Class Features

As a Wildkin, you gain the following class features

#### Hit Points
**Hit Dice:**                    :: 1d12 per Wildkin level
**Hit Points at 1st Level:**     :: 12 + your Constitution modifier
**Hit Points at Higher Levels:** :: 1d12 (or 6) + your Constitution modifier per Wildkin level after 1st

#### Proficiencies
**Armor:**   :: Light armor, medium armor, shields
**Weapons:** :: Simple weapons, martial weapons, fist weapons
**Tools:**   :: Herbalism kit, Leatherworker’s tools

**Saving Throws:** :: Strength, Consitution
**Skills:**        :: Choose three from Animal Handling, Nature, Perception,  Athletics, and Survival


#### Equipment
You start with the following equipment, in addition to the equipment granted by your background:
- (*a*) a martial weapon and a shield or (*b*) two martial weapons
- (a) a wooden shield or (b) any simple weapon
- An explorer’s pack and four javelins
    
### Primal Essence
*1st-level wildkin feature*
:
In battle, you fight with primal ferocity. When you make an attack, you may expend a use of your Primal Essence to enhance your attacks with Weave Essence.

- When you make a melee weapon attack using Strength, you gain a bonus to the damage roll that increases as you gain levels as a wildkin, as shown in the Primal Damage column of the Wildkin table.
- The damage dealt by this attack is magical
- The damage dealt by this attack cannot be healed by magical means, and can only be recovered through the use of a rest.

Once you have used an amount of charges equal to the number of times shown for your wildkin level in the Primal Essence column of the Wildkin table, you must finish a long rest before you can use Primal Essence again.

### Unarmored Defense
*1st-level wildkin feature*
:
While you are not wearing any armor, your Armor Class equals 10 + your Dexterity modifier + your Constitution modifier. You can use a shield and still gain this benefit.

### Essence Strike
*2nd-level wildkin feature*
:
When you roll a melee attack against a creature and miss, you may expend one use of your Primal Essence feature to instead guarantee a hit. You may use this feature a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and regain all uses at the end of a long rest.

### Guide of the Wilds
*3rd-level wildkin feature*
:
At 3rd level, your connection to the Wilds around you grant you the ability to commune with them. Choose the type of Guide of the Wilds you will be: **Winds**, **Lands**, **Stars**, or **Gods** Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th, 10th, and 14th levels.
\page
{{pageNumber,auto}}

### Ability Score Improvement
*4th-level wilkdkin feature*
:
When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can’t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.

### Extra Attack
*5th-level wildkin feature*
:
Beginning at 5th level, you can attack twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.

### Fast Movement
*5th-level wildkin feature*
:
Starting at 5th level, your speed increases by 10 feet while you aren’t wearing heavy armor.

### Stalwart Guide
*7th-level wildkin feature*
:
Starting at 7th level, your familarity with the Wilds around you grant you unparrelled feats of clarity. You gain the **Favored Terrain** Feature. You can choose from the following Terrians: arctic, coast, desert, forest, grassland, mountain, swamp,

While in this Terrian you gain the following features
- You cannot be **surprised**.
- You gain advantage on initiative rolls.
- You are immune to rough terrain or any other effect that would slow your movement.
### Destructive Might (d12)
*9th-level wildkin feature*
:
Beginning at 9th level,  your Primal Damage grows enhanced with the destructive might of the Weave itself. Your Primal Damage die becomes a d12.

This increases to a d20 at 13th level and a d100 at 17th level.

### Wild Fervor
*11th-level wildkin feature*
:
At 11th level, you connection to the wilds allows you to persist in combat. When you suffer damage as the result of an attack, you may make a free retalitory reaction to strike back at your foes.

This attack may not benefit from Primal Essence.
\column
### Destructive Might (d20)
*13th-level wildkin feature*
:
At 13th level, your Primal Damage increases beyond normal parameters. Your Damage die becomes a d20, and if the rolled value is below 10, you add 10 to the value of the roll.

This increases to a d100 at 17th level.

### Eternal Essence
*15th-level wildkin feature*
:
Starting at 11th level, your Primal Essence has grown in power. If you reduce an enemy to 0 hit points while using Primal Essence, you can choose to regain the charge immediately. You can do this a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus.

You regain expended uses after a long rest.

### Destructive Might (d100)
*17th-level wildkin feature*
:
At 17th level, your Primal Damage increases beyond what was thought possible by mortals. Your Damage die becomes a d100, and if the rolled value is below 40, treat it as a 50.

### Guiders Offense
*18th-level wildkin feature*
:
Your strength fuels you in unnatural ways as the Wilds take hold of your very life essense. You gain the following benefits.

- **Ability Score Increase.** Increase your Strength or Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 30.

- **Overcome Defenses.** The Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing damage you deal always ignores Resistance.

- **Overwhelming Strike.** When you roll a 20 on the d20 for an attack roll, you can deal extra damage to the target equal to the ability score increased by this feat. The extra damage’s type is the same as the attack’s type.

### Wildkin of Grattum
*20th-level wildkin feature*
:
At 20th level, your body interlaces with the weave, and the very life essence of the planet. 
- Your Strength, Consitution, and Wisdom scores are set to 30.
- You only have 1 Primal Essence Charge per day, but it applies **Vulnerability** to the next attack.
- Your Primal Damage die, increases to 1d500.


\page
{{pageNumber,auto}}

## Guide of the Earth
 Wildkin Guiders are highly sought after in combat, as their prowess on the battlefield allows them to perform many feats of strength.

Here are some of the Guiding Ways of the Wildkin you can choose from at 3rd level.
### Guider of the Winds
<!-- All attacks have the ability to push and pull enemies. Juggle combo from fighting games. fist weapon prof -->
Guiders of the Winds utilize the fleeting nature of the breeze to bring about the destructive force of a hurricane. Wind Guides are some of the most sought after fighters in Grattari Wars, for their unyeilding forcefullness in combat.
#### Weapon Proficiency
*3rd-level Wind Guide feature*
:
You gain proficiency with fist weapons. These ancient weapons can channel the power of unarmed strikes two fold. When you make an "unarmed" attack with a fist weapon, double all damage done to the target.

#### Breezey Bulwark
*3rd-level Wind Guide feature*
:
You gain Expertise in your **Unarmored Defense** Feature. You now add double your Dexterity and Consitution modifiers.

#### Gasping Gale
*6th-level Wind Guide feature*
:
Starting at 6th level, you can tap into the deeper recesses of your Primal Essence. If you expend a charge of your Primal Essence, you can choose to instead force a creature to make a Strength saving throw, pushing it 15ft in a straight line on a failed save. This movement *will* provoke attacks of opprotunity. 

If you sucessfully utilize your Primal Essence in this way, the charge is refunded back to you.

#### Typhoon Grapple
*10th-level Wind Guide feature*
:
Starting at 10th level, you can now harness the strength of the Winds to fuel your Primal Essence. If you expend a charge of your Primal Essence, you can choose to force the winds to pull any number of creatures within 30ft of you into melee range. The target makes a Dexterity saving throw, moving within 5ft of you on a failed save. This movement *will* provoke attacks of opprotunity.

If you sucessfully utilize your Primal Essence in this way, the charge is refunded back to you.
\column
#### Debilitating Draft
*14th-level Wind Guide feature*
:
Starting at 14th level, the Winds have granted you the ability to force the wind from the sails of all who would oppose you. When you make an attack, you can choose to expend a use of your Primal Essence to **stun** your foes. If you Stun a creature in this way, you regain your entire ***Action***.


