## Class Features
- Monk - Planetspeaker
  - Subclass Name: Clestial Voice
    - Voice of the Burning
    - Voice of the Slumbering
    - Voice of the Living
    - Voice of the Desolate

As a Planetspeaker, you gain the following class features

#### Hit Points
**Hit Dice:**                    :: 1d10 per Planetspeaker level
**Hit Points at 1st Level:**     :: 10 + your Constitution modifier
**Hit Points at Higher Levels:** :: 1d10 (or 6) + your Constitution modifier per Planetspeaker level after 1st

#### Proficiencies
**Armor:**   :: None
**Weapons:** :: Simple weapons, shortswords, fist weapons
**Tools:**   :: Choose one type of artisan’s tools or one musical instrument

**Saving Throws:** :: Wisdom, Constitution
**Skills:**        ::  Choose three from Acrobatics, Athletics, History, Insight, Religion, Medicine, and Stealth

#### Equipment
You start with the following equipment, in addition to the equipment granted by your background:
- (a) a shortsword or (b) any simple weapon
- (a) a dungeoneer’s pack or (b) an explorer’s pack
- 10 darts
    
## Celstial Voice
Being a Planetspeaker allows you to commune with the Celestial Bodies surrounding Grattum.

### Voice of the Burning (Father Sun)
Fire attacks, healing fire, Fire shield
### Voice of the Slumbering (Sleeping Child Moon)
Attacks that can sleep enemies, Slowing attacks. allows allies to get speedy rests
### Voice of The Living (Living Child Moon)
Attacks that life steal/life transfer, Can revive allies
### Voice of the Desolate (Dead Mother Moon)
Attacks that sunder enemy armor, desintergrate bodies/belongings
    
