# The Northlands     
{{pageNumber,auto}}


### Northpass
The Northpass is a wild untamed land in the furthest reaches of **The Northlands.** Home to Savages, Dragons, and other rumored monsters, it's a region of desolation. Many adventurers through the years have spent countless weeks attempting to map the region, only to return speaking on the folly of passing the Northern Mountain ranges. It is said passing the mountains are nearly, if not completely, impossible and any who seek to do so, only want for death.

It is not uncommon for many to believe in these rumors and try nonetheless, however, only a few have braves the terrors and ruthless battles the Northpass has to offer. Upon the World Map, Northpass lies within the deep reaches of the Northern Mountains, slightly dripping into the Westward forests of the Wendaren Wilds.

This land is not for the faint of heart. You will find no civilization, no respite, and no saftey in Northpass for any adventurers; Arcinite or Wanderer alike.
### The Blackwald

A Dense forest full of wildlife and fauna of both The Material Plane, and the Feywild. A mixture of dangerous and friendly creatures walk these lands, ripe for adventure and curiosity. Deep within the forest lies a clearing, that when viewed under the light of a full moon, one can see a series of druidic symbols making a circle around rapidly growing wolfsbane. Should any shape-changer or lycanthrope change states in this circle they may be cured of their ailment, or trapped forever; So the legends say... 
{{note
To the south lies a small hut built within a large Oak Tree. There lies the Feline Shifter Grimaia, or Grim for short. She sells a variety of magical items, scrolls, and custom healing potions (Made to order). She is more interested in the people who visit her shop and their adventures, than making any coin from them. Common is her second language so she speaks with a unique candor and takes unnatural pauses, almost trying to find the correct word, often. Although she is mainly posted to the south of The Blackwald, she can be found in any major city that has a nature district. She is fond of returning customers, especially if they have more interesting stories to tell.
}}

