<!-- Firemorn Town Info -->
### Firemorn
Although many adventurers pass through the small town of Firemorn, it has, through infamy or otherwise, become the defacto "Beginners Town." 

Dubbed as such by veteran Adventurers, they believe that the nearby Arcane Citadel allows many such goings-on to occur to help "train" their new Arcanite Recruits, and let any Wanderers test their might.

Although the townsfolk don't seem to mind the monthly kidnapping, or goblin attack, many believe there is something more going on...
#### **Population:** 
**Town:** 2769 (70% Humans, 18% Halflings, 7% Elves, 5% Other Races)
#### **Government:** 

The small town is governed by an appointed Mayor, whom reports to the “Keeper” of Storms Helm.

#### **Defense:** 
The city has little defense in the form of a citizen militia and volunteer warriors.

#### **Commerce:** 
Firemorn exports its agriculture throughout the surrounding areas, but mostly to Storms Helm.

<!-- The Blackwald Journey to Storm's Helm. Learned via rumors and piecemeal information -->
### Torm
Not much is known of the small island fishing village of Torm. Many visitors have called the town quaint and inviting. For adventurers, Torm is a relieving rest stop on the high seas before truly venturing into the unknown of the Northern Seas, or returning to the saftey of Storm's Helm.
#### **Population:** 
**Town:** ~950(60% Humans, 15% Halflings, 10% Gnomes, 10% Dwarves, 5% Other Races)
#### **Government:** 

The small town is governed by an elected Mayor, who bargins trade routes to Durax Keep and Storm's Helm.

#### **Defense:** 
The city has little defense in the form of a citizen militia and volunteer warriors.

#### **Commerce:** 
Torm exports its agriculture, fish, and unique delicacies through water-bound trade routes to the stronghold of Durax Keep, and their personal dock in Storm's Helm.

\page
### The Wendaren Wilds
The untamed wilds to the west and south of **Storm's Helm** are some of the most uninhabited lands acorss Fal'doren, and especially the Northlands. Many beasts, monsters, and nefarious factions find there home in these blanketed flat lands, forests, and mountain ranges.
:
Save for the might of **The Arcane Citadel**, no other sect of civilization has made it's mark within **The Wendaren Wilds**, marking it as the perfect testing bed for all up and coming adventuring types.
:
For the last few years, some recent adevnturing types have laid claim to some rumors that a small group of nomads have made small homes deep within the wilds, but no one has been able to verify these claims as of late. The only verifiable piece of knowledge is that of a "Wandering Merchant" who makes their home within large ***Ancients**,* massive trees that are nearly 500 years of age or more. It is said these trees originated from the **Faewild**, and were brought over with the events of **The Fracture,** but such accounts have been unproven.
### Durax Keep

#### **Population:**
**Stronghold:** ~200(35% Humans, 35% Elves, 15% Gnomes, 10% Dwarves, 5% Other Races)

#### **Government:**

Durax Keep reports to both Storm's Helm and Farendell of its location security.

#### **Defense:**
Durax Keep is heavily fortified with a metal-reinforced log wall, guard towers, and a singular double door entrance. A Large force of various military personel are stationed at the Stronghold.

