![The Lands Abound Spotify Code](https://github.com/PhantomDesk74/Homebrewery_Assets/blob/main/BookArt/The%20Lands%20Abound.png?raw=true) {position:absolute,bottom:40px,right:65px,width:250px,filter:opacity(70%);}

\column
# The Lands Abound
::
### The Wender Marshlands

A sprawling assortment of waterways, muddy paths, and aquatic beasts of all sorts have claimed this land as their own. Acting as one of the only passages to and from **The Northlands**, The Wender Marshlands act as a natural barrier to any outsiders. This, in turn, makes the guard trade highly lucrative to any would-be adventurers hoping to expand their reach via assisting Traders crossing the Marshlands.

Throughout the Marshlands lie many folk-tales and rumors of various druidic cirlces and tribesfolk. Though many of these rumors have been unconfirmed, many still take caution when traveling through the Wender Marshlands, for none truely know what lurks in the muck...

### Farendell
The tight knit city of Farendell holds many different walks of life in its walls. **"The Glory Hole,"** as it is so unsavorously named, is the Cities premiere fighting ring and primary form of commernce. Any and all travelers beyond and within the walls may fight for "Gold and Glory," but the real intrigue is the city life outside of the ring. Bustling trade districts and gulidhalls make an honest living within the city, waiting for those to browse their wares.

#### **Population:** 
**City:** ~72,000 (35% Humans, 25% Elves, 20% Dwarves, 15% Half-Races, 5% Other Races)
#### **Government:** 

This Large City is governed by an appointed "Herald." Residents know this leader as only a figurehead, as crime seems to run rampant in the city, and the various theives guilds "run" the city.

#### **Defense:** 
The city has a large defensive force in the form of: City Watch, Sea-facing artillery, and Capital Punishment for crime.

#### **Commerce:** 
Farendell is a gamblers delight. Much of the commerce generated by the city lies within the fighting pit. Tourists and Residents alike can bet for or against fighers and the "city" takes a cut off the top of the total winnings.



