<!--https://i.imgur.com/jqLdugx.png -->


### The Ashen Forest
This decrepid wasteland is barren of all life. Infested with the plague of undeath and void of all living flora and fauna, **The Ashen Forest** is one of the most deadly places on the planet. Countless citizens, adventuerers, and curious historians have perished in its lands with no hope of escaping it's grasp. Nestled deep within the forst are the remains of the **Necrodrake,** a twisted creature emanating undeath from it's decaying corpse.
:
Rumors of dark mages and untold evils have begun to spring up in recent years. Whispers of shrouded figures seemingly searching for this forbidden relic of the past have come to many who travel the path near the forest. No one seems to know the reason for these figures' search, but many can suspect it is not for a righteous cause.
:
A small sect of Death Priests and Necromancers of **Chemosh** reside within the Forest, attempting to keep its undead denizens at bay from encroaching on the lands of the living. Through their efforts, fledgling adventurers are able to cross the scar unharmed, trade routes have been resecured, and some semblance of peace has been brought back to the **Burnwood** and the **Jasper Wilds**.


{{note
#### The Lakewood
To the East of the **Burnwood**, past the **Ashen Forest**, lies the mystical **Lakewood**. Home to many of the orphaned **Miristarian Druids**, the Lakewood holds a large sect of druid clans. This mystical forest gets it unique name from the "Lake-like" island filled with trees grown by an unknown druid. The only known identifier of these trees are an ancient signature in druidic carved on to nearly every tree.
}}
### Jasper Wilds
The rolling hills and grasslands of the **Jasper Wilds** are home to all different sorts of inhabitants. From hidden hovels filled with gnomes and halflings, to the traveling village nomads of Orcs, the Wilds offer many different cultures and new faces to meet. One of the largest unbroken prairies in the land, the Wilds are truly a holy land to many Druid Circles and enthusiatsts of nature, many of whom wish to share the beauty and knowledge of the land around them. While most adventurers won't find maidens to save, or beast to slay, there is still so much history felt within the very blades of grass that sway beneath every footfall.


\page
{{pageNumber,auto}}

### Port Toela
As one of the major distributers in Fal'Doren for fish, farm, and livestock, **Port Toela** is well known as the home of the **Guild Bearers.** This faction deals heavily in Commerce, Manufacturing, and Distribution, making Port Toela the perfect outsourcing location.

Throughout the Lands Port Toela is known for it's unique City Scape, as it runs deeper inland than any other Port city. While the typical city runs along about a mile or two inland, Port Toela boasts a massive 15 mile stretch of land that consists of smaller hovels, farms, and livestock storages. While these small "Towns" don't necissarily have names, many of the people are happy to call themselves citizens of Port Toela.

#### **Population:** 
**City:** ~95,000 (35% Humans, 30% Genasi, 15% Halflings, 15% Gnomes, 10% Other Races)

#### **Government:** 
Like many Port Cities, an "Admiral" sits as the primary governing force for the city. Uniquely, this Admiral is actually democratically appointed via a majority vote every Fall and Spring Season

#### **Defense:** 
Large watch towers and guard patrols protect the inland interests. Large City walls, a City Watch, and Sea facing Cannons protect the city from any threats of assault.

#### **Commerce:** 
While Port Toela is primarily a navel shipper, it owns land as far as 15 miles inland. This land is stocked with vineyards, agricultural farms, and livestock storages. Port Toela is one of, if not *the* most profitable city in the Lands. 

