# The Lands Afar
:
### Terris
Many adventurers pass through the small town of Terris, but having one of the largetst outputs of novice adventurers, it's rare to see verteran adventurers make their way back.

The neighboring Metropolis of **Solstice** provides a constant outflux of new Wanderers to make their way into the larger world. While Terris is on the bigger size of Towns, it still has its own unique intrigue for the new to adventuring types.
#### **Population:** 
**Town:** ~7300 (45% Humans, 30% Elves, 15% Dwarves, 10% Other Races [Mostly Halflings, Tieflings, and Genasi])
#### **Government:** 

The town is governed by an elected Mayor.

#### **Defense:** 
The city has a moderate defense in the form of a Elven Guardsmen and multiple Watch Towers

#### **Commerce:** 
Terris exports its fishing hauls and small agriculture to Solstice and to other port cities, like Storm's Helm

### The Shard Spires
As the ancestral home of the Dwarven Clans of Fal'Doren, the **Shard Spires** are a colossal range of mountains that span miles of land further than most can see. While the Dwarven clans made their home deep in the caverns of the mountains centuries ago, the Capital **Atlas** is a major monument to all denizens of the world set in the southern base of the range. 

To the Southwest, the location of the famed **"Lord of Storm's Final Stand** can be found. As such, the Shard Spires boast a large amount of tourist and religious visitations. Although the path to "the Stand" is a relatively easy path, once arrived, many find it difficult to not be overwhelmed with the great presence that persists there. 

![The Lands Afar Spotify Code](https://github.com/PhantomDesk74/Homebrewery_Assets/blob/main/BookArt/The%20Lands%20Afar.png?raw=true) {position:absolute,bottom:40px,right:65px,width:250px,filter:opacity(80%);}

