### Lonard's Stand
A Large Stone Arch was erected in the place of death as a monument to one of the greatest mortal heroes of the realm. While Lonard only recently became a god, this monument is considered to be the first true holy site of the Fourth Prime Diety. When approaching the monument, many emotions course through the body of all who choose to make the journey.

Conflicting reports upon visiting the Stand have be said to bring about feelings of Hope, Sadness, Respect; others have said it makes them feel Weak, Small, and Introspective. 

{{note
*"To stand on the same ground a God walked... it feels mystical in it's own right. But to see the ground, the grooves in the earth, to know the a battle took place here and the earth itself still is reeling... that feels more powerful and real than any religious painting or statue.*

-- The words of a Traveler
}}

### Tarrel Desert

Once the beautiful sprawling **Tarrleyan Forests**, The Tarrel Desert is one of the greatest changes brought about by The Fracture. A truly empty place, the Desert has no discernible landmarks, only rolling dunes as far as the eye can see. In the Southwest of the Desert, the Salen Oasis is the only form of respite from the swealtering sands.

Over the years, many people have sought answers to the question of where the Forests went, but no answers have been found. Expeditions have been made to create excavation sites, in search of what lies below the sands, but reports have confirmed that nothing lies below 25 feet of sand. These reports don't mean metaphorically, they mean literally nothing; Once a hole is dug exactly 25 feet deep, a black hole opens in the sands and swallows anyone unlucky enough to be nearby, the surrounding sands refilling the hole within the next few minutes.

Roaming bands of Bandits, Wardens, and Pirates ward off would be treasure hunters and archeologists. They consider their methods a mercy, even if violent. Pain is a powerful deterrent...


