\column

### The Slab

A barren, desolate white sheet. The Slab is a tundra with no life and seemingly no entrance or path into its waste. Before the Fracture, the Slab was nearly unreachable, boasting a sheer cliff face directly into the Western Straight nearly 100 meters tall before solidifing into ice and sleet. Now, Horizon's Shadow allows a path to the Slab for the first time.

First reports confirmed general suspicions of The Slab: a frozen waste with mountians of ice, hidden valleys beneath massive pockets of snow, and crevasses stretching hundreds of feet deep. It it highly reccommended to not venture into the Slab without proper equipment or guides, it seems like there is no reason to adventure this far north...

### Horizon's Shadow

Heading Northward past the **Shard Spires**, Horizon's Shadow only exists in part due to **The Fracture.** Although recently mapped, Horizon's Shadow was once the highest peaks of the Spires, but now turned into a ruinous rocky mass. It serves as a cobbled pathway to **The Slab,** the northern most ice slate that reaches the main continent of Fal'Doren.

Horizon's Shadow has also made its infamy through the inadvertent destruction of the **Western Straight,** a critical trade shipping route through crossing between the Ter'ak Sea and The Western Shores. After the events of the Fracture, many societies to the west suffered as a result. The solution to this new found conundrum was to create new land routes until a suitable sea route could be reestablished.

As of today, not many creatures or denizens make their homes within the Shadow, causing it to hold the same desolate nature as the Slab. Recently treasure hunters, relic collectors, and historians alike have begun to make expiditions to the Shadow in the hopes of finding any uncovered mysteries since the shifting of the mountains. Others have used this new found path to make way for the Slab and see what it might have to offer the world.

