     Use --rotation to set rotation angle in degrees. -->
# Salen Oasis
In the deep south of the Tarrel Desert, the Salen Oasis is the only form of respite and civilization in the endless heat and rolling dunes. While many travelers make the pilgramage from **Port Toela** through the **Jasper Wilds**, most deniznes of the Oasis actually reside within the Sands themselves.
:
Most travelers to the Oasis come for the fabled stories of the Origins of the mythical "Miristar," the ancient (and now dead) secret order of Druids and Covert Operatives. While not much is known of their exploits, the Oasis is the prime source of information as many relics of the Tarrleyan Forests were saved and brought to the Oasis after ***The Fracture.*** 
#### **Population:** 
**Metropolis:** ~175,000 <!-- ~1.5 M -->(40% Various Genasi, 30% Humans, 15% Dragonborn, 10% Tieflings,5% Other Races)
#### **Government:** 

Small Government regins supreme in the Salen Oasis. Trade Princes, Water Barons, and Various Warlords all "vie" for control of the Oasis. The many factions within the Oasis have created some form of a hierarchy for leadership, but the citizens can never figure out who is at the top. 
{{note
All of these Governing bodies secretly work together to protect the secret city beneath the sands. The war is for show, as all of the "Deaths" are either faked or pre-planned with individuals with terminal illnesses or with criminals who have been coerced or dominiated to their demise.
}}
#### **Defense:** 
The City is not fortified, nor guarded very well. Many petty crime is harshly punished by the many gangs and factions roaming the streets, enacting an old sort of "Wild West" Lawlessness.
#### **Commerce:** 
While crime is scarce within the Oasis, traders, gypsies, and crafters find their mark on the commonfolk. Local business is the leader in commerce for the Oasis, and imported contraband is highly valuable.
