### Heurn
#### The Grand Chronicler
:
##### Alignment {{width:100px}}  Domains
###### Chaotic Good {{width:90px}} Knowledge, Forge,
###### {{width:195px}} Order, War

::
<!-- ADD DESCRIPTION -->
Every story has a begining; Every Fable, its end. Through all spoken and written accord, a single  being binds them all to a single tome of history: Heurn. **The Grand Chronicler** is the God of Tradition, History, and Family. Followers of Heurn typically come from close knit family, or a long lineage of generational followers. 

Temples of Heurn are the only of the Prime Dieties to be wholly build, run, and maintined by a family legacy. Whereas normal Prime Temples are run by organizations, Heurn Temples act more like a public library run by the likes of a "typical mom'n'pop shop."

:
The Holy Symbol of Heurn is the only Holy Symbol to be dynamically implemented across Rakktenn. It will always included a <u>**large open tome, the spine facing downwards, with a campfire erupting from the pages. 4 silhouettes of various races are within the fire.**</u>
