# What Are Adventurers?
:
As heroes of old, Adventurers are the lifeblood of Fal'Doren. As Protectors of the Realm, Adventurers are considered to be the greatest front of the forces of Good. Plenty of Adventurers make their start in Taverns, Mercenary employ, or even just being in the right place at the right time to prove their heroics.

Although Adventurers may belong to a large swath of organizations, kingdoms, or factions, the Lands of Fal'Doren have taken to categorizing Adventurers into two different sub-sets: **Wanderers**, those who have gotten their start in the world by venturing into the Wilds and becoming bastions of hope; and **Arcanites**, those who have devoted themselves to the famous Arcane Citadel, an Adventuring academy that acts as the largest Adventuring Guild in Fal'Doren.

### The Wanderers
Heroes known as **Wanderers** are those who have chosen the path of old. Classic Adventuring types who met by happenstance and decided to charge forth into the unknown together with allies and friends they have made along the way. Many old storied tales of Adventurers were actually Wanderers themselves, marking Wanderers as the "true" adventurers in some circles.

### The Arcanites
**Arcanites** however, are the opposite side of such a coin. With the backing and resources of **The Arcane Citadel**, Arcanites have many advantages to assist them in their travels. The world views Arcanites as Trained heroes, those willing to put in the time and effort to avoid any unwanted mishaps and mistakes. To this end, many see Wanderers as sufficient adventurers, but may be more inclined to take the curated nature of an Arcanite.

No matter where you go in the world, an Arcanite can be sought and found. Job Boards and Quest Hubs alike seek them out due to their reknown and fame related to their Patron **Alistair Stormweaver**.
:
In Adventuring circles, Wanderers and Arcanites alike have a rivalry with one another similar to that of fighting siblings. Both understand their worth in the world, yet refuse to agree on who is ahead, and who is behind.

\page
{{watermark WORK IN PROGRESS}}

{{pageNumber,auto}}
# Heroes of Old
**Heroes of Old** are adventuring parties all throughout the Lands of Fal'Doren that have gained their noteriety through many different means. They regularly traverse the Lands seeking to change the world around them in one way or another. Should you ever find yourself in the company of such Heroes, take full advantage and create memories with some of the greatest Fal'Doren has to offer.

While some Heroes of Old are true Parties, others are considered a Classification of Heroes, such as the famed **Veteran Novices.** These heroes make it their mission to foster the fledgling adventures in towns like Firemorn or Terris, choosing to forgo their full potential in exchange for making a lasting difference in the lives of other adventurers.

Below you will see the descriptions of various Heroes of Old:
## Gintooth Deliveries
*Created by Drew Costello*

### Description

- Karl Gintooth
- Johanes Gintooth
- Werner Gintooth
- Petter Gintooth
- Ingvar Gintooth

### Claim to Fame
They really gained their fame when during a delivery, they helped a local farm stave off a goblin raid. For a whole week, these 5 dwarven heroes kept waves of goblins from burning down the buildings that they were sheltering in with a family of halflings.

 On the 5th night, Karl himself managed to sneak past the goblins keeping watch over the farm and ran 2 hours to the nearest town to muster a militia to take back the farm. In the morning, he returned with 75 men to break the encampment and liberate the farmers.
 
 The brothers were hailed as heroes! This also marks one of the few times that they had failed to deliver a shipment, but they have long since made back the money for the lost shipment in gifts and free drinks. 
### Major Accomplishments
They started their adventures as basic couriers, delivering carts of goods and sundries. They are know to be some of the best, most reliable and trustworthy couriers in the land.  They have a nearly perfect delivery record, and they have been at it for over 30 years.

They travel along established paths, only straying when a delivery or pick up requires it. Their cart has a stylized toothy grin with lips painted on it in bright colors. It is usually pulled by an mule that the brothers have affectionately named Herlig (dwarven for beautiful).

The brothers still primarily work as couriers, but they will always step up if someone is in danger.
### The Gintooth Route
The Gintooth route is the famous route the brothers take from the deepest reaches of the Lands Afar, starting at Mirist Respite, and travelling as far west as Farendell and Port Toela! Should you encounter the brothers on their route, feel free to share up to date information on the road ahead! If you're lucky enough to find them resting at one of their stops, buy them an ale as a token of appreciation.

