# The Arcane Citadel 

The Arcane Citadel is a revered institution that serves as a hub for aspiring adventurers, regardless of their class or background. Located in any prominent city or town, the guild's many headquarters stand as an iconic landmark, recognizable by its prominent banners and symbol that signify a safe haven for those seeking challenges, camaraderie, and training.


Built in the year 885 E.E., Aspiring adventurers from various walks of life flocked to The Arcane Citadel, drawn by the opportunity to hone their skills and gain knowledge under the tutelage of experienced mentors and seasoned adventurers. In Modern Times, the guild offers a wide range of training facilities, including combat arenas, spellcasting chambers, archery ranges, trap-laden dungeons for rogue training, and more, catering to the diverse needs of different classes.

{{descriptive
##### At the helm of The Arcane Citadel
Alistair Stormweaver, a legendary figure renowned for his expertise in combat, magic, and wisdom. As the guildmaster, he oversees the operations and ensures that every member receives equal opportunities to grow and excel as adventurers.
}}

The guild’s reputation is not solely based on Alistair’s prominence but rather on the countless adventurers who have risen to fame and accomplished great deeds after receiving training within its walls. This legacy has made The Arcane Citadel a prestigious organization that attracts the attention of quest-givers, nobles, and those in need of heroic aid. Inside The Arcane Citadel, members can find camaraderie with fellow adventurers, access valuable resources, seek guidance from mentors, and embark on missions dispatched by the guild. Beyond the halls of training, the guild also houses a vast archive of ancient maps, artifacts, and lore, which provide leads for potential quests and exciting adventures.

The Arcane Citadel becomes a central hub for Adventurers, offering them a plethora of opportunities to grow, learn, and prove themselves in the ever-changing world of Fal'Doren. From battles and quests to friendships and rivalries, this guild sets the stage for countless thrilling adventures.

## Academy Perks
With the Arcane Citadel as your group’s patron, you gain the following perks. The Citadel pays for the work you do on its behalf. The nature of your employment influences your compensation. On average, the Citadel pays each member of your group 1 gp per day, or enough to sustain a modest lifestyle. Alternatively, you receive a bounty (at least 250 gp) for each artifact or relevant discovery you bring back from your adventures and donate to the Citadel's Archives.

#### Accommodations.
You can stay at your organization’s guildhall. The rooms are comparable to those in a comfortable inn, but at a modest price (5 sp per day). Splayed throughout the continent are “safe-housing” areas within towns, cities, and metropolises that can be discerned by the Guild Symbol/Phrase (**A Black Crystal Wand with a Blue Circle Background or “Sil’me tu Rak’me Peno Fal’dormo”**)


#### Equipment
You can requisition the use of specialized tools, laboratories, libraries, or other crafting space and equipment to use within the Citadel. When you make an ability check with a set of any specialist’s tools using the Citadel’s equipment, add double your normal proficiency bonus to the check.

#### Resources
The Citadel hosts libraries, museums, record repositories, and training facilities, and you can use them to further your work. You can call in a favor from faculty members to access resources not available to the public—dangerous relics or magic items, spellbooks, gear, and the like. Additionally, you can consult with the faculty of the Citadel as the experts in various fields.

#### Training
The Citadel retains knowledgeable tutors in subjects pertinent to its interests. When you undertake the training downtime activity (as described in the Player’s Handbook and Xanathar’s Guide to Everything), the training takes half as long. The DM decides if the Citadel has tutors available for a given subject.

![Arcanite Sigil](https://github.com/PhantomDesk74/Homebrewery_Assets/blob/main/BookArt/Arcanites.png?raw=true) {width:275px,mix-blend-mode:multiply}

{{artist,bottom:100px,right:60px
##### Symbol of 
##### The Arcane Citadel
}}
<!--
### Guild Contact
Even as a member in good standing of the guild, you can’t simply stroll up to the guild master and demand their attention. Your superiors within the guild manage work contracts, request the use of guild resources, and facilitate getting your group in contact with the right people to assist their interests.

### Attentive Overseer
A guild representative takes personal interest in your group’s tasks. They follow your exploits and know of your adventures before you return to report. Despite the unsettling depth of their knowledge, they seem genuinely eager to shepherd your work. -->


