# Character Options
Listed throughout this section is a multitude of character options that are available for your players. Each section is detailed below to inform you how intricate each section can be. From Race Options, Hero Classes, Character Origins, Mythical Feats and Class feats, and even the Mythical Magic Items, you'll be able to find everythin you need.

## Hero Classes

Hero Classes are meant to be mid-late game archetypes that can be unlock via a special event. Unless specified, Hero Classes act as a "mask" on top of your original class selections. For instance, **The Maledicter** Hero Class can only be taken afer 10 level, meaning any class features you would have gotten for your class from levels 1-10 will be included in *all additional* class features obtained via The Maledicter.

{{note
Example:

You are a 10th Level Fighter, who then becomes a Maledicter. You keep all Fighter Hit points, Features, and Class abilites up to 10th level. From 11th Level on, you will no longer gain any Fighter Features, but instead follow the Maledicter path for the remainder of your characters' life span. Multi-classing post Hero Class selection is unavailable.
}}

## Race Options

While the world of Fal'Doren is vast, it is not limitless. Some races found in official and supplimental D&D 5e books will be unavilable in this setting. As such some restrictions have been put in place to help maintain narrative. A few additional Races have been included for character options, and you may even find a few rare NPCs touting such races.
\column
## Character Origins

Character Origins are an experimental option for character creation. They offer expanded power early on in a character's development and help create pre-adventuring narrative hooks. Consult your DM before you choose one of these options, as some may or may not fit within the overarching narrative being told.

## Mythical Feats

One of the most powerful aspects of Character Growth within Fal'Doren is the addition of Mythical Feats. More powerful than published offical Feats, Mythical Feats are custom tailored to be as powerful as possible, with the added caveat that they can't be chosen, only rewarded.

## Mythical Class Feats

Following the same concepts as Mythical Feats, Class Feats are Class specific. All class feats are made with the desire to include all subclasses. Whereas traditional feats may attempt to focus power into a specific archetype, Mythical Class Feats can be used by the Classes, and not specifically their Subclasses.

All classes benefit in some way from their Class Feats, enhancing their base abilites and allowing them to become even more powerful versions of themselves.

## Mythical Magic Items

Mythical Magic Items, are just that, *Myth.* These items are nearly impossible to obtain, being locked away in extraplanar vaults, wielded by Gods themselves, or simply lost to time. While they are certainly "obtainable," coming into possesstion of one may take the course of an entire campagin, or seeking them out with surgical precision over the course of multiple large adventures.

\page
<!-- Fighter/Druid Combo-->

{{pageNumber,auto}}

{{wide,text-align:center
# Hero Class: The Maledicter
}}
*Prerequisite: Mark of the Miristar Mythical Feat, 10th Level, and Champion of a Miristar Diety.* 

**Once gifted, you will cease gaining levels in classes other than Maledicter.**

{{classTable,frame,decoration,
