| 19th  |  +6  | Ability Score Increase    | 
| 20th  |  +6  | Tarrleyan Maledicter | 
}}


## Class Features

As a Maledicter, you gain the following class features in addition to your base class.

### Hit Points
**Hit Dice:**                    :: 1d12 per Character level
**Hit Points at 1st Level:**     :: 12 + your Constitution modifier
**Hit Points at Higher Levels:** :: 1d12 (or 7) + your Constitution modifier per Character level after 1st

### Proficiencies
**Armor:**   :: All Armor, shields
**Weapons:** :: Katana, Bowstaff
**Saving Throws:** :: Dexerity, Wisdom
**Skills:**        :: Choose three from Acrobatics, Deception, Insight, Persuasion, Athletics, Investigation, Survival

### Spellcasting Ability
{{text-align:center
**Spell save DC**:: = 10 + your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier

**Spell attack modifier**:: = your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier
}}

### Fighting Style
You adopt a particular style of fighting as your specialty. Choose one of the following options. You can’t take a Fighting Style option more than once, even if you later get to choose again.

#### Blind Fighting
You have **blindsight** with a range of 10 feet. Within that range, you can effectively see anything that isn’t behind total cover, even if you’re blinded or in darkness. Moreover, you can see an invisible creature within that range, unless the creature successfully hides from you.

#### Dueling
When you are wielding a melee weapon in one hand and no other weapons, you gain a +2 bonus to damage rolls with that weapon.

#### Superior Technique
You learn one maneuver of your choice from among those available to the Battle Master archetype. If a maneuver you use requires your target to make a saving throw to resist the maneuver’s effects, the saving throw DC equals 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Strength or Dexterity modifier (your choice).

You gain one superiority die, which is a d6 (this die is added to any superiority dice you have from another source). This die is used to fuel your maneuvers. A superiority die is expended when you use it. You regain your expended superiority dice when you finish a short or long rest.

### Ancestral Warrior
Starting at 2nd level, you may call upon knowledge of other Miristar to aid you in battle. When you finish a long rest, you may take one of the following class features. It will last until your next long rest:
{{two-column-list
- Action Surge
- Rage
- Wild Shape
- Inspiration
- Sneak Attack
- Lay on Hands
}}
Utilizing one of these Class Features allows it to scale to your relevant Character Level.

### Multi-attack
Starting at 5th level, gain the **Multi-attack** feature, allowing you to intertwine multiple weapons, multiple spells, or a mix of martial/arcane prowess. 

When you take the attack action, you can choose to attack up to 3 times. If you instead choose to use a spell, you may instead target *double* the amount of targets listed.

Additonally, you can instead choose to cast a spell *and* attack once with a weapon you have in your hand.
\page


### Glancing Blow
Starting at 7th level, you gain the ability to stave off blows before they can do meaningful damage. Whenever you are hit with an attack or spell, make a Dexterity Saving throw with a DC of half the damage dealt to you. 

If you succeed, you take no damage, as the attack glances off your blade or armor. You may use this feature an amount of times equal to your proficiency bonus and regain all uses on a short or long rest. 

{{pageNumber,auto}}
<!-- {{watermark WORK IN PROGRESS}} -->

### Miristar Teachings
Starting at 9th level, when you finish a long rest, you may choose two class features from the **Ancestral Warrior** Class Feature.

### Ceaseless Counter
Starting at 10th Level, you make it increasingly difficult for enemies to fend you off. Any time an enemy misses a melee attack, ranged attack, or casts a spell against you, you make take a free reaction counter attack back at them.

This attack can be a weapon attack or a spell. This reaction only be a basic weapon attack and cannot benefit from any class features or modifiers. The spell will be cast at its lowest level and cannot be up-cast.

### Mutli-attack
Starting at 11th level, you can attack 4 times, instead of 3, whenever you take the attack action on your turn. 

In addition, you may cast 2 leveled spells, target ***quadruple*** the listed targets, *and* have 1 attack with a weapon.

### Ancestral Tradition
Starting at 13th level, you can call upon the knowledge of the Miristar Ancestors to gain Expertise in a weapon you are proficient in, applying that bonus to your weapon attack and damage rolls.

If you critically strike using this weapon, utilze the table below to determine the outcome of the wound you inflict. This effect lasts for 1 round.

As a spell caster, you instead choose 1 cantrip of your choice that requires a spell attack roll. This cantrip gains these abilities. (i.e. If you choose Shillelagh, your spell attack modifier is doubled with proficiency.)

##### Weapon Critical Table
| 1d6 | Effect |
|:------------------:|:-----:|
| 1 | Paralyzed | 
| 2 | Stunned| 
| 3 |  Prone   | 
| 4  | Incapacitated   |
| 5  | Bleeding   |
| 6  | Dead   |

### Phantom Strike
Starting at 15th Level, you gain the ability to cut down countless foes. When you make an attack, you can choose to chain that attack to a number of enemies equal to your proficiency bonus. To Begin your Phantom Strike, determine the amount of targets you will be attacking, then average *all* of their Armor Classes into a single Difficulty Check. Make an amount of attacks equal to half of the amount of enemies, rounded down. If even 1 attack hits, all enemies are affected.

##### Phantom Strike Damage Table
| Attack Roll | Damage/Effect |
|:------------------:|:-----:|
| Natural 20 (Critical)| Target Instantly dies | 
| More than 10 over AC | 1/2 Max HP value in damage| 
| More than 5 over AC  | 1/2 Current HP value in damge     | 
| More than 3 over AC  | Double Damage (Critical Hit)    |
| Hit Target           | Weapon DMG + Fighter/Druid Level     |

Upon hitting with Phantom Strike, all enemies are afflicted with 1 condition of the Maledicter's choice: **Stunned**, **Paralyzed**, **Blinded**, or **Incapacitated.**

You can use this ability 3 times per long rest.

### Miristar Mastery
Starting at 17th level, when you finish a long rest, you may choose four class features from the **Ancestral Warrior** Class Feature.

### Grasp of Tarrel
At 18th Level, each time you make a weapon or spell attack, erupting vines attempt to bind your foes. Enemeies must make a Dexterity Saving throw against your spell save DC, becoming **Restrained** on a failure.

### Tarrleyan Maledicter
At 20th Level, you can assume the form of an ancient Tarrleyan Maledicter Avatar. Using your action, you undergo a transformation. For 1 hour you gain the following benefits:

- You gain ***all*** abilities from your **Ancestral Warrior** Class feature.
- You become immune to all non-magical attacks.
- Any attacks that hit you have at 1/3 chance to do 0 damage.
- Any spells cast at 4th level or lower cost no spell slots.
- Any healing you recieve is doubled in value.
- You become immune to the following conditions: **Paralyzed**, **Blinded**, **Deafened**, **Incapacitaed**, **Charmed**, **Restrained**, **Grappled**, **Stunned**, **Frightened**, and **Stunned**.
:
Once you use this feature, you can’t use it again until you finish a long rest.


\page

<!-- Warlock/Wizard Combo -->
{{pageNumber,auto}}
{{wide,text-align:center
# Hero Class: The Hellborn
:
*Prerequisite: Victim of an Activated Contract for an Archdevil with an Heir Clause.*
**Once discovered as a Hellborn, you gain Hellborn levels in tandem with your normal class levels.**
}}

{{classTable,frame,decoration,wide
##### Hellborn
