| 18th  |  +6  | - | 4 | 15 | 5 | 9th |
| 19th  |  +6  | Ability Score Increase    | 4 | 15 | 5 | 9th |
| 20th  |  +6  | Damned if you Do, Damned if you Don't | 4 | 15 | 5 | 9th |
}}


## Class Features

As a Hellborn, you gain the following class features in addition to your base class.


### Hit Points
**Hit Dice:**                    :: 1d10 per Character level
**Hit Points at 1st Level:**     :: 10 + your Constitution modifier
**Hit Points at Higher Levels:** :: 1d10 (or 6) + your Constitution modifier per Character level after 1st

### Proficiencies
**Armor:**   :: Light Armor
**Weapons:** :: Whip, Sickle, Dagger
**Tools:**   :: Torturer's Tools
**Saving Throws:** :: Charisma, Intelligence
**Skills:**        :: Choose three from Arcana, Deception, Persuasion, Acrobatics, Investigation, Medicine

### Spellcasting Ability
{{text-align:center
**Spell save DC**:: = 10 + your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier

**Spell attack modifier**:: = your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier
}}
::

### Hellfire Blood
At 1st Level, the Infernal Contract's Heir Clause permenantly changes your phyisology, warping you to become more hellish in nature. Your Race changes to Teifling, and your sub-race of Teifling is that of the Archdevil who was the Benefactor of said contract.

### Bound by Law
At 2nd Level, you are bound by contract to enheirit the lands and powers of your Benefactor. You gain immunities and resistances based on your Benefactor, and can no longer be affected by the following conditions.

|Archdevil|Infernal Boon|
|:-------:|:------:|
|Zariel | Immune: Radiant Damage/Max Health Reduction Effects|
|Dispater | Immune: Deception/**Detect Thoughts** |
|Mammon   | Immune: Silence Effects|
|Belial/Fierna   | **Dominate Person** Free Cast |
|Levistus | Immune: Cold Damage |
|Glasya   | Truesight 120ft |
|Baalzebul| Immune: Charm Effects/Domination Effects|
|Mephistopheles | Resistant: Magical Effects/Damage|
|Asmodeus | All Infernal Beings are Allied to you |

\page
{{pageNumber,auto}}

### Hellborn Caster
At 3rd Level, you gain access to hidden Hellborn Spells to enchance your Infernal Prowess. when you reach a Hellborn level specified in the Hellborn Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.

##### Hellborn Spells
| Hellborn Levels | Spells| 
|:---------------:|:-----:|
| 3       | Flame Blade, Invisibility, Ray of Enfeeblement, Darkness|
| 5       | Bestow Curse, Fear, Summon Lesser Demon, Vampiric Touch| 
| 9       | Conjure Elemental (Fire), Cloudkill, Danse Macabre, Contagion| 
| 13      | Fire Storm, Finger of Death, Power Word Pain, Simulacrum    | 
| 17      | Foresight, Psychic Scream     |

### Soulless
*6th-level Hellborn Feature*
:
Being claimed by the Hells has its benefits. While your Bloodline has changed, you soul is now absent. With this emptiness now inside you, you can become incorporeal. 

Whenever you are the target of a spell or attack, roll 1d10. On a 5 or higher, the attack misses entirely. You can use this ability a number of times equal to your Charimsa modifier + your proficency bonus ***during combat.*** After combat is complete, you regain all charges.

### Infernal Empowerment
Starting at 10th Level, you now add double the value of both your Charisma and Intelligence modifiers to your spell damage rolls.

### Bound by Blood
*11th-Level Hellborn Feature*
:
Blood is a powerful tool within the Hells. It can be an even greater power in the Material Plane. If you create a **Blood Pact** with a creature, you gain the following benefits:
- While within 30ft of your Bond, you gain a +3 to AC and +1 to *all* saving throws.
- You and your Bond are immune to the **Charmed** condiditon.
- Whenever your Bond would suffer damage, you can reduce that damage by your Charisma modifier + your character Level.

However, your bond suffers the following effects:
\column
- Your Bond is soley devoted to you, and cannot be swayed opposite your opinions.
- They will brazenly defend your honor, to the death.
- They will do whatever it takes to gain your favor, no exceptions.
- They can't help but be obesssed with your every action.

To End a **Blood Pact** your Bond must **die.** If the target of your Bond is attempted to be resurrected, there is a 30% it will fail, and their soul will be consumed by the Hells.

### Tainted Knowledge
*13th-level Hellborn Feature*
:
The teachings of the Hells, and the torturous screams of the damned have unlocked a secret potential within your mind. With your head burning and scratching you gain the ability to fling forth infernal knowledge congruent with your Benefactor. You may freely cast the spell associated with your Benefactor below, as if it were a cantrip.

|Archdevil|Knowledge|
|:-------:|:------:|
|Zariel | Holy Aura|
|Dispater | Maze|
|Mammon   | Finger of Death|
|Belial/Fierna   | Foresight |
|Levistus | Wall of Ice |
|Glasya   | Mass Suggestion |
|Baalzebul| Harm|
|Mephistopheles | Antimagic Field|
|Asmodeus | Power Word: Kill |

### Hell Hath No Fury
At 14th Level, your inheritance grants you the full powers of your Hellish Domain. You may Summon a Devil that fits the Domain of your Benefactor. The Devil you summon has additonal abilities that follow:
- The Devil shares all boons granted by **Bound By Law**
- The Devil Gains 1 Spell of your choice from your highest Castable spell from **Hellborn Caster**

|Archdevil|Devil(s)|
|:-------:|:------:|
|Zariel | Pit Fiend|
|Dispater | 2x Erinyes |
|Mammon   | Amnizu |
|Belial/Fierna  | 12x Barbed Devil |
|Levistus | 3x Ice Devil |
|Glasya   | 4x Horned Devil|
|Baalzebul| Moloch |
|Mephistopheles | Hutijin |
|Asmodeus | Zariel |

\page
### Public Defender
*15th-level Hellborn Feature*
:
As more aspects of the Hells seep through into your persona, you can become much more convincing. Your Blood Pacts become more powerful and unlock additonal bonuses:
- While speaking alongside your Bond, you gain advantage on all Charisma checks.
- While your Bond is advocating on your behalf, you can cast **Charm Person**, **Friends**, or **Dominate Person** without requiring any spell components.

However, your Bond continues to suffer:
- Your Bond struggles to find the right words, and speak logically without emotion. They have disadvantage on **Persuasion** checks.
- Your Bond can't help but defend you, and your blood empowers them. They are **immune** to non-magical attacks.
- Your Bond becomes emubed with dormant **Hellflame**. You can choose to ignite this flame, killing your Bond and dealing 10d10 Hellfire Damage to all creatures within 10ft of your Bond. Hellfire **cannot** be put out, and burns for 1d6 days.

{{pageNumber,auto}}
### Hatred Incarnate
*17th-Level Hellborn Feature*
:
As the taint of the Hells permeates through your veins, your physiology continues to become more devilsh in nature. You gain the following features and traits:
- Your Charisma and Intelligence scores increase to 20 if they aren't already.
- Your Strength Score increases to 24 if it isn't already.
- Your feet morph into hooves, granting you 20ft of extra movement
- Your hands morph into claws, granting you 2d6 slashing damage on unarmed attacks.
\column
### Damned if you Do, Damned if you Don't
*20th-level Hellborn Feature*
:
As the sole ruler of your respective Layer of the Hells, you must write and sign various contracts to maintain your power and status. Doing so will grant you the following abilites:
- You gain access to the **Wish** Spell.
- Once a day, summon forth **Bountiful Riches**: 100k gp in gems and other artifacts.
- Summon up to 3 devils a day, whose Challenge Rating is less than or equal to your Player Level.

Abstaining from writing or signing contracts will invoke the following penalties:

- You maintain a minimum of 2 levels of **exhaustion**.
- Devils will no longer be allied to you or your party.
- Lesser Devils from your plane of rule, will regularly attempt to usurp you.

For every Contract you write and sign, you gain 1 type of **Short-Term**, **Long-Term**, or **Indefinite Maddess**.
:
When you create a contract, you can write in a **Duality Clause**. A Duality Clause allows for the *Benefactor* (You) to not only gain the profits of the *Consideration*, but to also gain ***all Benefits*** pertaining to the *Offer.* Additionally, you are **exempt** from any and all *Breach of Contract* clauses should the *Signee* fail to meet the contract.

The more contracts you write and sign, the more power you can obtain. However, should any contracts be nullified for any reason, you lose all power accumulated with said contract in perpetuity and retroactively.


\page
{{pageNumber,auto}}


