## Valenar Elf

Your people are dedicated to the arts of war. Millenia ago, your ancestors fought an epic war against mighty giants. When they came to Khorvaire, they battled the champions of the goblin empire. The greatest heroes of those struggles live on after death, known as the patron ancestors. When you became an adult, one of the patron ancestors formed a bond with you. Now it is your duty to follow in the footsteps of your patron, living your life as they lived theirs, allowing this champion to live on through you. This is why your people constantly seek out conflict; you need to find challenges worthy of a hero.


#### Valenar Elf
A Valenar elf gains proficiency with the scimitar, double scimitar, longbow, and shortbow.

### Valenar High Elf

#### Ability Score Increase
Your Intelligence score increases by 1.

#### Cantrip
You know one cantrip of your choice from the wizard spell list. Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for it.

#### Extra Language
You can speak, read, and write one extra language of {{width:50px}}your choice.

### Valenar Wood Elf

#### {{width:55px}}Ability Score Increase
{{width:65px}}Your Wisdom score increases by 1.

#### {{width:115px}}Fleet of Foot
{{width:120px}}Your base walking speed increases {{width:120px}} to 35 feet.

#### {{width:120px}}Mask of the Wild
{{width:120px}}You can attempt to hide even when {{width:110px}} you are only lightly obscured by {{width:90px}}foliage, heavy rain, falling snow, mist,{{width:80px}} and other natural phenomena.

## {{width:75px}}Slayer Dwarves
{{width:70px}}Deep within the slopes of the Shard Spires,{{width:65px}} lies a small sect of Dwarves known as{{width:65px}} Slayers. These exiles live in solitude, {{width:65px}}looking to attone for the sins of their past.
:
{{width:130px}}Any who seek to leave the sect{{width:130px}} must be branded with the {{width:130px}}*Slayer's Mark*. This ancient{{width:130px}} Dwarish Sigil shows all who {{width:145px}}meet the Slayer that they are{{width:150px}} an exile, and one not to be trifled with. The Slayer's Mark also imbues the dwarf with supernatural abilities.



### Slayer Traits
As a Slayer Dwarf, you have the following racial traits.
#### Creature Type
You are a Humanoid.

![homebrew mug](https://www.dndbeyond.com/attachments/4/122/311.png) {position:absolute,bottom:5px,left:-130px,width:380px,transform:scaleX(-1)}

