- asdasdasd

 -->

### Weavesown
Becoming touched by the very essence of the Weave, you gain the ability to grasp the literal fabric of magic. With it, you can glimpse into the seam of The Weave and peer into alternate realities.
 - You can now perceive and interact with **Shatter Warps**, tears within the fabric of The Weave.
- You gain the **Weavesense Skill**. The ability modifier you use for this skill is **Wisdom**, and you have immediate Proficiency in this skill.
- You gain Proficiency in Weaver's Tools
 
 ### Mark of the Miristar
*Prerequisite: Must be a Samurai Fighter of Heurn **or** Star Druid of Sylvvanas*
:
The Miristar and your own personal experiences have left you with great power surging within you. Choose one of the following creature types: **Abberation**, **Undead**, or **Fiend**. </br>
If you study a creature of your selected type for at least 1 minute outside of combat, you gain the following benefits.
:
- All attack rolls you make against that creature are at advantage.
- All saving throws you make to save against a spell originating from that creature are at advantage.
- If you are the only enemy within melee range of the creature, all attacks it has against you are at disadvantage.
- If you score a critical hit on a studied creature, you make 2 additional actions against the creature. This effect stacks.

### Spelldriver
*Prerequisite: Character level 8th or higher*
:
Through intense focus, training, and dedication you've harnessed the technique of rapid spellcasting. You are no longer limited to only one non-cantrip spell per turn. However, should you cast two or more spells in a single turn, only one of them can be of 3rd level or higher.
\column
### Master Chef
The mark of a Master Chef is that of a party member who can fill the bellies of their allies to perfection. As a Master Chef you can gain knowledge of cooking from other Master Chefs throughout the land. The more you learn, the higher your rank in cooking is.
##### Tier 1: Apprentice
 - Gain Proficiency in Cook's tools
 - Gain the ability during a long or short rest to create "**Home Cooked Meals.**" Anyone who consumes these meals gains 5 temporary hit points until their next rest.
##### Tier 2: Journeyman
- Can cast **Goodberry** 1/day without expending a spell slot
- Gain Expertise in Cook's tools
- **Home Cooked Meals** now give 10 temporary hit points until a short or long rest.
##### Tier 3:Expert
- Cna Cast **Goodberry** 3/day without expending a spell slot
- Can no longer roll below a 10 when making an ability check while using Cook's Tools.
- **Home Cooked Meals** now additonally give 1 point of ***Inspiration.***
##### Tier 4: Artisan
- Can cast **Goodberry** 5/day without expending a spell slot
- Can cast **Hero's Feast** 1/day without expending a spell slot or requiring the monetary materials.
- When making **Home Cooked Meals,** you can now make "**Left Overs.**" These act like Tier 1 Home Cooked Meals that can be consumed as a bonus action.

\page

### Lore Keeper
Your immense thirst for knowledge has allowed you to amass a large amount of knowledge to add to your repertoire. You gain the **Keen Mind** Feat and all its features. Additonally, you gain the following abilites:

- Gain Expertise in **History**
- Any check that is attempting to specifically recall a piece of history or world lore cannot roll lower than a 14. It is up to the DM if your character would know of the particular subject.
- Once per 30 in game days or 6 real life months (whichever comes first), you can reach into the recesses of your mind to obtain seemingly forgotten knowledge from your hours of study. You may ask the DM 1 question pertaining to your journey, and they must answer truthfully.


{{pageNumber,auto}}

### Titan's Grip
*Prerequisite: Dual Wielder (2014) Feat, Strength 16 or higher*
:
Utilizing your enhanced Strength offers you the ability to wield ever greater weapons.
- You may now Dual Wield weapons with the **Two-Handed** property.
- All attacks made can now add your ability modifier to the damage rolls.

### Hustler
Spending countless hours winning and losing coin in alestained taverns has forged you into a consummate gambler and chance-seeking addict. You gain the following benefits and features:

- Increase your Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- You gain proficiency with two types of gaming sets of your choice.
-  You have advantage on Charisma (Deception) checks to bluff opponents in games of chance, and Charisma (Persuasion) checks to convince others to join you for a game.

- You have a reputation as a card shark in some circles. Some folks may avoid playing you for this reason, while other gamblers may seek you out specifically.

- When you take the Carousing or Gambling downtime action, you may reroll your result once, but must keep the results of the second roll.

### Precise Punishment
*Prerequisite: Strength or Dexterity of 18 or higher*
:
Your advanced experience in martial combat have allowed you to sunder your foes armor, shatter their weapons, and cripple their resolve. Before you make an attack on a foe, you may choose to gain disadvantage on the roll. If you hit, choose from one of the folowing effects based on the weapon damage type.

- Bludgeoning
  - **Sunder Armor:** Reduce target's AC by 1 until repaired.
  - **Shatter Armament:** Roll a d10. 1-4: Weapon gains -2 to attack rolls / 5-10: Weapon is destroyed
- Piercing
  - **Pinned**: Restrain a target's limb or body to a surface.
  - **Stuck**: Cause the target to bleed for 1d10 for 1d4 rounds.
- Slashing
  - **Cripple**: Cripple a target's limb making it unusable.
  - **Blind**: Permenantly Blind the target.

### Weave Threader
*Prerequisite: 12th level Spellcaster*
:
Utilizing the endless expanse of The Weave, you rewrite the fabic of magic to converge two spells. You may choose from two prepared spells, but to combined total for each spell cannot exceed 6th level. All spells will be cast with their base level effects. Below is an example of some spell combinations and the resistance and immunity effects.
##### Convergance Spells Examples
| New Spell Name | Spells Used | Damage |
|:--------------:|:-----:|:-----------------:|
| Voltic Flare      | Fireball + Lightning bolt     | 8d6 Fire/Lightning   |
| Solar Barrage     | Magic Missle + Scorching Ray  | 3d6 Fire/Force       |
| Volley of Ic      | Ice Knife + Ice Storm     | 4d6 Piercing/Cold        |

{{note
*Resistances and Immunity Note:* If a target has resistance to one or both of the listed damages refer to this smaller calculation

- 1 Resistance: **Takes 1/4 less damage** 
  - (i.e. Resistant to fire, but not lightning: 40 total damage from Voltic Flare, would take 30 damage, as the lightning half of the spell was resisted)

- 2 Resistances or 1 Immunity: **Takes 1/2 less damage**

- 2 Resistances and 1 Immunity: **Takes 1/4 of total damage**

- 2 Immunities: **Takes no damage**

}}







