{{wide,text-align:center
# Mythical Class Feats
}}

{{pageNumber,auto}}

### Lonard’s Thirst
*Prerequisite: Barbarian with a minimum 16 Strength*
:
While your Raging Aura is active, half of all damage delt by your aura, returns to you as healing.

- You can now choose to make your melee attacks while raging deal Necrotic Damage


### Battle Theme
*Prerequisite: Bard with a minimum 16 Charisma*
:
Your prowess in the arts matches that of the battlefield. Once every 7 days, you may choose to activate ***Real Time Combat***, a feature that removes turn based combat. Inititative will be rolled, then you will begin combat. You may pick any song that you wish to play for the combat. It's duration must be a minimum of 3 minutes and a maximum of 7 minutes.  After the song has completed, all combatants will take exponential damage each round until a side is victorious.

When you activate this feature, you may choose to forgo your turns during combat entirely to grant yourself and party the following ablilities:
{{classTable,frame
##### Real Time Combat Boons
| Song Genre/Type | Bard Bonus | Party Bonus |
|:-----------------:|:-----:|:-----------------:|
|    Heavy Metal    | Disadvantage on *ALL* attacks against you | Advantage on *ALL* attacks against foes  |
| Classical         | Any allied healing in a 120ft radius is *MAX* | *ALL* incoming damage is halved     |
| Rock               | You gain 4x your inspiration total. It can be doled out at will     | Inspiration Die can't roll lower than half value on the die.                |
| Somber             | You cannot be stopped by direct damage.     | Gain a *Permenant* **Sanctuary** Spell effect.                |
| Uplifting             | Cause all foes within 60ft of you to become **Feared**.   | Gain Immunity to All Conditions                |
| Meditative            | You gain vulnerability to all damage, but if you remain unharmed, you gain the benifits of a long rest     | All enemies gain resistance to your damage, but if you succeed in combat, you gain the benifits of a long rest                |

}}
If you are ever interrupted during your **Battle Theme**, make a Concentration (Consitiution) Saving Throw. If you fail, return to turn based combat, then follow ending song rules for 2 rounds.
\column

### Tutelage of Timera
*Prerequisite: Cleric with a minimum 16 Wisdom*
:
Seeking the Guidance of The Tutor is the most opportune moments, you have been granted her favor.
- You learn the **Guidance** Cantrip, and it doesn’t count as one of your learned class spells.
- The **Guidance** cantrip now becomes a 10ft aura that is active only outside of combat. Should you provide help to an ally within this aura, they gain advantage on their ability check and cannot roll below a 10.

### Wild Child
*Prerequisite: Druid with a minimum 16 Wisdom*
:
The Wilds have brought you great strength to enhance your abilities. You obtain the following attributes

- Gain proficiency in the **Nature** skill
- You have a natural sense of direction. You can never be lost in the Wilderness and travel time through the Wilderness is the same as if you were traveling along a road or path.
- Once per Long rest, you may cast the **Entangle** Spell without expending a spell slot. Foes have disadvantage on their saving throw when you cast the spell in this way.

### Dueling Master
*Prerequisite: Fighter with a minimum 16 Dexterity or Strength*
:
As a master of Martial Prowess, you have gained the ability to decimate enemies in one-on-one combat. You may choose 1 foe in combat a number of times equal to half your Fighter level, rounded down. Your target must succeed on a Charisma Saving through or suffer the following effects:
- Target suffers as if affected by **Compelled Duel**
- Target cannot escape the duel by any means

If at any point during the duel, you or the foe attempt to attack or interact with any other creature, they will "lose" the duel. When the duel is completed, the victor regans all hit points lost during the duel.
\page
{{pageNumber,auto}}


### Chakra in Check
*Prerequisite: Monk with a minimum 16 Dexterity*
:
Mastering the Inner Self, you sap the life from your enemies to fuel your own attacks. When you score a critical hit against an enemy, you gain 1 **Opened Chakra.** You can hold a number of Opened Chakra equal to your Wisdom + Dexterity Modifiers. Expending an Open Chakra can grant you one of the following effects:
- Whenever you would use one of your **Ki Features**, you may use a second at the same time.
- When you would cause an enemy to roll a saving throw, give them disadvantage on the roll.
- When you need to roll your Martial Arts die as a part of your Ki Feature, double the amount of dice used.
### Templar
*Prerequisite: Paladin with a minimum 16 Charisma and 14 Strength*
:
Your devotion to the divine has granted you the abillity to freely smite your foes into oblivion. You may expend your **Channel Divinity** to gain **Templar's Verdict**.
#### Templar's Verdict
For 1 minute, you gain a number of Divine Smite charges equal to your Charisma bonus. When you use Divine Smite in this way, treat all creatures as if they were undead. Additionally, you cannot roll lower than half the value of your Divine Smite damage die.
### Strider
*Prerequisite: Ranger with a minimum 16 Dexterity*
:
Your familiarity with your surroundings and the thrill of your hunts have pushed you to heights previously thought unobtainable. At the start of every week, choose one of the following features to obtain:
- Your **Favored Enemy** expands to 5 creature types.
  - All Attacks against Favored Enemies are at Advantage.
- Your **Favored Terrain** expands to 5 terrain types.
  - Party Travel Speed is doubled in your terrains.
- Your **Primevil Awareness** feature can detect ***all*** creature types, and you can decern types and exact distances from your position.
  - You are immune to Divination Magic originating from any creatures in your range.
### Seasoned Scapegoat
*Prerequisite: Rogue with a minimum 16 Dexterity*
:
Your fleet footed nature allows for easy escape in all situations. You gain the following abilities:
- You have advantage on **Deception** checks when attempting to con your way out of a situation.
- You have advantage on all **Stealth** checks when you are fleeing.
- If you utilize the **Disengage** action as a part of your **Cunning Action** feature, you may also **Dash** as a part of that same action.
### Loose Lineage
*Prerequisite: Sorcerer with a minimum 16 Charisma*
:
Your bloodline is as viscus as the blood in your veins. You may choose at the start of a new day to embrace the bloodline of a different Sorcerer Subclass. For every Sorcery point you expend, you gain a 5% chance to succeed on changing your Subclass with no adverse reactions. Roll a d100: on a failure, roll 1d4 3 times, and succumb to one of the following effects for each roll. If you roll a duplicate number, the effect stacks.

- Gain 1 level of exhaustion
- Gain 1 Short Term Madness
- Lose 5 Spell Slots for the day
- Reduce your Max HP by 1/4 of your base total health.
### Pact Breaker
*Prerequisite: Warlock with a minimum 16 Charisma*
:
While you may have made your own pacts, nothing can truly hold bond over you. 

Following a long rest, choose one of your other **Pact Boon** options and gain all of its features in addition to your original **Pact Boon**. This will remain as your additional Pact Boon for the remainder of the day. 

You may use this feature of number of times equal to your charisma bonus, after which you must wait 1 month to use the feature again.
### Mighty Mind
*Prerequisite: Wizard with a minimum 16 Intelligence*
:
Your mastery of study and ingenuity have granted you additional arcane protections. You gain the **Wall of Protection** Ability. It can be used a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier + your proficiency bonus.
#### Wall of Protection


**Casting Time:** :: 1 reaction
**Range:**        :: 15ft radius / 30ft Line centered on yourself
**Components:**   :: S
**Duration:**     :: 1 round

All allies in a 15ft radius or 30ft line horizontal to you gain a +3 to AC until the start of your next turn.

