{{wide,column-count:2

#### Mera’kan Moonblade
*Longsword, Mythical Artifact (requires attunment from an Elf or Half-Elf of Any Good Alignment)*
:
This Moonblade has been within the **Moonbryn** family for millenia. It holds great power within it, and when wielded by a worthy decendant, it can unlock its full potential. The blade has had 9 previous owners, all of whom have imbued the sword with a sliver of themselves. When attuned to this weapon you gain the following traits based on the weapons connection to you.
:
##### 0 Runes
- **Sentience:** A moonblade is a sentient neutral good weapon with an Intelligence of 16, a Wisdom of 18, and a Charisma of 14. It has hearing and darkvision out to a range of 300 feet. The weapon communicates by transmitting emotions, sending a tingling sensation through the wielder’s hand when it wants to communicate something it has sensed. It can communicate more explicitly, through visions or dreams, when the wielder is either in a trance or asleep.
:
- **Personality:** Every moonblade seeks the advancement of elvenkind and elven ideals. Courage, loyalty, beauty, music, and life are all part of this purpose. The weapon is bonded to the family line it is meant to serve. Once it has bonded with an owner who shares its ideals, its loyalty is absolute.
:

\column
##### 3 Runes
- You gain a **+1** bonus to damage and attack rolls made with this weapon.
- When you hit with an attack using the ***moonblade***, the attack deals an extra **1d6** slashing damage.
- You gain the **Temperate** Feature. The bearer suffers no harm in temperatures as cold as -20 degrees Fahrenheit or as warm as 120 degrees Fahrenheit.

##### 6 Runes
- You gain a **+2** bonus to damage and attack rolls made with this weapon.
- The ***moonblade*** scores a critical hit on a roll of 19 or 20.
- You gain the **Key** Feature. The item is used to unlock a container, chamber, vault, or other entryway.


##### 9 Runes
- You gain a **+3** bonus to damage and attack rolls made with this weapon.
- The ***moonblade*** functions as a **defender**.
    - The first time you attack with the sword on each of your turns, you can transfer some or all of the sword’s bonus to your Armor Class, instead of using the bonus on any attacks that turn. For example, you could reduce the bonus to your attack and damage rolls to +1 and gain a +2 bonus to AC. The adjusted bonuses remain in effect until the start of your next turn, although you must hold the sword to gain a bonus to AC from it.
- A **Hidden Message** appears on the blade when all runes are activated. 
