{{monster,frame
## 'Johnny O'
*Medium Human, any alignment Barkeep*
___
**Armor Class** :: 10
**Hit Points** :: 11 (1d10 + 1)
**Speed** :: 30 ft.
___
|STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA|
|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
|12 (+1)|10 (+0)|12 (+1)|8 (-1)|14 (+2)|16 (+3)|
___
**Saving Throws** :: Con +3, Cha +5
**Skills** :: Insight +4, Perception +4, Performance +5, Sleight of Hand +2
**Senses** :: passive Perception 14
**Languages** :: Common, +2 Additional Languages
**Challenge** :: 1 (200 XP)
___
**'Johnny O'** is the name given to *most* barkeeps within the Lands. Unless a barkeep wishes to keep their name known for any reason, feel free to introduce yourself to 'Ol Johnny O'. This tradition orginally started as a joke from a few members of the Guild Bearers faction, during which time in the city of Farendell, 2 twin siblings ran a popular pub together.

Johnny would run the bar in the mid morning to mid afternoon, and his brother Joeseph would take over at night. The pair would consistently fake who they were, leaning into perposterous rumors that 'Johnny O' would never sleep, but only watch the bar.
}}

{{monster,frame
## Mayor Clask
*Medium Human, Lawful Evil*
___
**Armor Class** :: 10
**Hit Points** :: 6 (1d8 -2)
**Speed** :: 25 ft.
___
|STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA|
|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
|9 (-1)|10 (+0)|7 (-2)|14 (+2)|12 (+1)|16 (+3)|
___
**Saving Throws** :: Cha +5, Wis +3
**Skills** :: Persuasion +5, Deception +5, Performance +5, Sleight of Hand +2
**Senses** :: passive Perception 13
**Languages** :: Common, Giant
**Challenge** :: 1 (200 XP)
___
Mayor Clask is an exploitative and manipulative narcissist. Installed as the Mayor of Terris by the Thieves Guild, Clask consistently manipulates the market in his favor, and blindly ignores the public demand for a harsher crack down on crime.

In fact, Clask turns a blind eye to most wrong doings within the town as a whole. While the Guard may arrest criminals, they're usually back out on the street within a few days time. While Clask may seem untouchable, there are those in the Thieves Guild that are starting to regret their appointments.
}}

