{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:12px,color:Black Should The Signee fail To Strike This Line, The Signee may be required to serve The Administrator of Benefactor on a Single Task of the Administrator's Choosing.}}

:
{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:15px,color:Black This CONTRACT is made and entered into by and between {{width:10px}}{{font-size:16px,font-family:SolberaImitationRemake **Jefferson Clancy**}}{{width:10px}} (hereinafter the "Signee") and {{width:10px}}{{font-size:16px,font-family:old_evilsregular Hutijin}}{{width:10px}}(hereinafter the "Administrator") on behalf of the archdevil {{width:10px}}{{font-size:16px,font-family:october_crowregular **Mephistopheles**}} {{width:10px}} (hereinafter the "Benefactor") on this {{width:5px}}**21st** {{width:5px}} day of {{width:5px}}**872 P.F.** {{width:5px}} year.}}
:
{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:15px,color:Black Whereas, the Signee intends to purchase from the Administrator, and the Administrator wishes to offer an infernal service ("Offer") to the Signee, soley upon the terms of this contract. Whereas, the Administrator is the manufacturer, distributor, and/or provider of the Offer.}}
:
{{font-family:unquiet_spiritsregular,font-size:25px,color:Black,font-weight:bold I. Consideration }}
{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:15px,color:Black The Signee agrees to exchange the following property ("Consideration") in exchange for the Duties provided by the Administrator: {{font-size:12px,font-family:old_evilsregular Personal Everlasting Soul and/or Bloodline of Firstborn}} }}
:
{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:15px,color:Black Whereas, Consideration is under the sole ownership of the Signee. Whereas, Considertation will be surrendered immediately or at a time of the Administrator's choosing, unless Consideration is designated to be paid de futuro, which must be written on the reverse side of this document prior to sealing this Contract. }}
:
{{font-family:unquiet_spiritsregular,font-size:25px,color:Black,font-weight:bold II. Duties of the Administrator}}
{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:15px,color:Black The Administrator agrees to grant the Signee the following Offer:}}
:
{{font-size:12px,font-family:old_evilsregular 30 years of prosperous and fruitful labors to fully support and provide for Singee's Kin and Bloodline, up and until a minimum of 10 Generations.}}
:
{{font-family:unquiet_spiritsregular,font-size:25px,color:Black,font-weight:bold III. Breach of Contract }}
{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:15px,color:Black The following represent a breach of contract on behalf of the Signee:}}

{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:15px,color:Black i) Failure to surrender Consideration at time of collection}}

{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:15px,color:Black ii) Entering into conflicting or overlapping agreements with other beings}}
:

{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:15px,color:Black Should the Signee be found in breach of contract, the Signee immediately forfeits their soul or equivalent payment determined by the Administrator or a higher-ranking devil during Arbitration, to the contract Administrator to do with as the Administrator so choose.}}
:
{{font-family:unquiet_spiritsregular,font-size:25px,color:Black,font-weight:bold IV. Heir or Heriess Auxiliary }}
{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:15px,color:Black In the event of the untimely death or Divine/Infernal reclimation of the Mortal Coil of The Signee prior to the completion of the Offer by way only other than "Natural Causes", the Signee hereby recinds any and all claims to the Firstborn of the Signee's Blood Line (hereinafter the "Heir or Heriess", respectfully). The Heir/Heriess and all relevant assets are then transfered in full ownership to the Benefactor to become a "Hellborn."}}
:
{{font-family:dungeonregular,font-size:15px,color:Black This "Hellborn" will have equal and true claim to the Benefactor's assets and infernal seat as a true Heir/Heiress when they come of adult age, relevant to their original Bloodline. If no other claim is present, the Heir will take the Benefactor's place in the event of the death of the Benefactor, and the Consideration will be returned in full to the Signee, if applicable.}}
